    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">DfE Sign-in<br/><span class="gias-news-heading--date">31 October 2018</span></h2>
    <p>
        The way you log in to Get information about schools (GIAS) is changing. DfE Sign-in replaces Secure Access and users must migrate to this new accreditation system when instructed.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong class="bold-small">If you do not have a Secure Access username and password you do not need to take any action &ndash; you will continue to use GIAS as you do now.</strong>
        This migration to DfE Sign-in does not see any other change to how the GIAS service works.
    </p>
    <p>
        When you attempt to login to the GIAS service, you will receive a prompt to migrate, you will do this by entering your <strong class="bold-small">Secure Access <u class="bold-small">Username</u> and <u class="bold-small">Password</u></strong>. On screen instructions will
        then clearly explain and guide you through the process. You cannot dismiss or ignore this requirement but it is a one-time exercise, after which, you will no longer use Secure Access to login to GIAS.
        You may continue to use Secure Access for other services but these will also migrate in the coming weeks.
    </p>
    <p>
        Each organisation has a Secure Access approver. The approver in each organisation will still need to use Secure Access to manage who can login to GIAS and any other services. When all services have migrated to DfE Sign-in, approvers will receive further information.
    </p>
    <p>
        There may be minimal disruption to the GIAS service as we apply these changes on the morning of 1st November. If disruption becomes more extensive, we will provide an update on this news page. Users who encounter any
        difficulties after this time should contact the DfE Sign-in Helpdesk.
    </p>
    <p>
        We welcome your feedback as this helps us continue to improve the GIAS service &ndash; please complete our <a href="http://www.smartsurvey.co.uk/s/Getinformationaboutschools/" target="_blank">survey</a>.
        To help us prioritise and sort your feedback, if you have comments regarding DfE Sign-in please provide it using this <a href="https://help.signin.education.gov.uk/contact/form" target="_blank">feedback form</a>.
    </p>
    <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--m govuk-section-break--visible"/>

