    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Updating records to use services linked to Secure Access<br/><span class="gias-news-heading--date">26 October 2017</span></h2>
    <p>
        Secure Access requires users to update and/or confirm that their ‘EduBase’ record is correct within specified time periods. Until this action is completed, the availability of other services (including S2S, COLLECT, RAISE/ASP) that are controlled by Secure Access will be limited.
    </p>
    <p>
        As Get information about schools (GIAS) is now live, it is your establishment GIAS information that you should update. You should read references to ‘EduBase’ in this process as GIAS.
    </p>
    <p>
        To update your establishment information on GIAS please do the following:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>Log into Secure Access and make sure that you are on your account home page</li>
            <li>Click on Get information about schools in your list of available services</li>
            <li>You should then be taken to your establishment information page on GIAS. If instead you are taken to a public search page for the site you will need to click on ‘Log in’ at the top of the page (you should see this in a black margin). Provide your Secure Access login details and this will take you to your establishment information.</li>
            <li>Check your establishment details and you should now be able to edit them</li>
            <li>Edit your establishment information if necessary</li>
            <li>If you are satisfied that your establishment information is up to date, confirm the details. There should be a confirm details button either in the ‘Details’ tab on your establishment information page or just above the ‘Details’ tab</li>
            <li>Go back to Secure Access once you have confirmed the details. Refresh your page by pressing F5 or clicking on the ‘Home’ button at the top of the page</li>
            <li>Your establishment details will be correct and you should have access to your services again.</li>
        </ul>

    <p>
        If the above does not work or you require further assistance then please let us know by logging a web form here:
        <a href="https://form.education.gov.uk/fillform.php?self=1&form_id=AH8ogiDeAfD&noLoginPrompt=1">https://form.education.gov.uk/fillform.php?self=1&form_id=AH8ogiDeAfD&noLoginPrompt=1</a>
